{"title":"PNW Fern is a Kid’s specific dropper post with a low pressure cartridge for little riders!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/03/pnw-fern-is-a-kids-specific-dropper-post-with-a-low-pressure-cartridge-for-little-riders/","date":1630676955000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270336\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Your MTB prodigy already has a killer mountain bike. But what about that seat post? If you’re like us, you couldn’t live without a dropper post. It’s only fair that your kid gets one too, right? Thanks to PNW, there’s a new option for kid’s mountain bikes that’s actually built with little riders in mind…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding.jpg\" alt=\"PNW Fern kids dropper post\" width=\"999\" height=\"649\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding.jpg 999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-800x520.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-768x499.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding.jpg 999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-800x520.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093244/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-riding-768x499.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Just like kid’s suspension, a kid-specific dropper post needs to work for lighter riders. You might be able to slap a standard dropper post on a kids bike, but the seals and air spring tuned for heavier riders may make it harder for your young one to operate. That’s why the PNW Fern has a light weight sealed cartridge meant for riders between 44 and 110lbs. It’s important to note that those weights are the minimum and maximum supported weights of the post.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions.jpg\" alt=\"PNW Fern kid's dropper post sizing\" width=\"712\" height=\"549\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions.jpg 712w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions-297x229.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions-120x93.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 712px) 100vw, 712px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions.jpg 712w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions-297x229.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093242/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-dimensions-120x93.jpg 120w\"></a></p><p>In terms of size, the post is only offered in 27.2mm diameter with a 90mm travel. The chart above should help you figure out if it will fit your kid’s bike.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1.jpg\" alt=\"PNW Fern kid's dropper post external routing\" width=\"860\" height=\"828\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1.jpg 860w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-297x286.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-800x770.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-120x116.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-768x739.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 860px) 100vw, 860px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1.jpg 860w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-297x286.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-800x770.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-120x116.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03093239/PNW-Fern-Kids-dropper-post-externall-routed-1-768x739.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Since most kid’s bikes probably won’t have internal dropper post routing, PNW has gone with an external routing design for the Fern. The post doesn’t include a lever, but it’s compatible with all PNW levers and “most levers from other brands”. The 7075 aluminum post has a claimed weight of 506g.</p><p>Priced at $199.99, the post includes the same great Lifetime Warranty as other PNW products.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pnwcomponents.com/collections/shop-all-droppers/products/fern-dropper-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>pnwcomponents.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"47aae42ae5b0a28f5d2badfe6816a8533dcf4cc48d8aa2c07628de760eca9d69","category":"Cycling"}